我一直很喜歡你的部落格!但是我叫DaWenna Blevins 我是台灣的人

[I always liked your blog! But I’m DaWenna Blevins, I’m Taiwanese]

切利！

The people who face difficulty the most are definitely the ones who have been raised in a “Taiwanese” environment since young but then they come to the age where they make a decision to study abroad or even move overseas.

Previously actually without much awareness they would have been offended if you used any english on them, even when they understood culturally.

It is rather internal. Everyone in Taiwan has this subconscious pressure to sound local. Unfortunately as for those who grow up in the younger generation who have not been raised to speak “Taipei-ese”, they can’t even use the language properly.
